Sep 14 2009 	Pretty good for a reasonable price	I rate the hotel as above average because comparing it to those around the same price bracket (not expensive for London), I feel it performed well.The receptionist was very friendly when I phoned to confirm our booking a few days before, very friendly when we arrived, and again on check-out. This may be expected, but is certainly not always the case.Our room was clean and just what we needed. An extremely comfortable (reasonably firm) double bed. We were staying for one night after a gig at Wembley Stadium (for which this hotel is perfectly placed, just one tube stop and a couple of minutes walk away). The bathroom was clean and new-looking, the shower was hot and powerful. The bathroom was small, and the door didn't quite lock, but it didn't stop it serving our purpose.The breakfast was very good, and even the cooked items were put out buffet-style, which was very efficient as it meant no waiting around. I watched the dining room staff and they didn't miss a beat in clearing tables quickly, and topping up all breakfast items, juices, crockery and glassware. And in bringing tea and coffee They were polite - possibly not friendly as such - but it all ran very smoothly, and we didn't require any more than that and well cooked breakfast, which it was. The buffet set-up meant less waste, too, I think, as I didn't take more than I could eat, but it meant those with large appetites could keep going if they wanted to. There was also a good choice of cereals and - if I remember rightly - continental style items, too. And a choice of juices.Frognal is a busy area, so we felt safe walking back from the tube at night, but the hotel is just off a side street, so was very quiet. And there was a Pizza Express on the way to the tube, so ideal for eating something on the way to Wembley if not wishing to face their queues or prices!The room was fine, not huge, but how big do you need a bedroom to be?? And the light switches were crazy, so it was hard to find the right light. It was like a trick! But that's a minor downside for one night. May have driven me mad if we were there for longer!Would stay there for the same kind of trip again.	
